## Performance — Dynamic Imports

Use `next/dynamic` for heavy AI-related components.

```typescript
import dynamic from "next/dynamic";

// Monaco Editor is heavy — always lazy load
const MonacoEditor = dynamic(
  () => import("@/components/features/review/MonacoEditor"),
  {
    ssr: false,
    loading: () => <EditorSkeleton />,
  }
);

// Terminal animation on landing — not needed on other pages
const TerminalAnimation = dynamic(
  () => import("@/components/features/landing/TerminalAnimation"),
  { ssr: false }
);
```

